The paper discusses integration problems on Open Data Platforms, which involves dealing with large amounts of data from various domains and authors. This suggests a focus on database management (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. The mention of crowd-based data integration techniques also suggests a focus on social computing (cs.SI) and software development (cs.SD) for implementing these methods. Finally, the mention of standards and domains suggests a focus on cybersecurity (cs.CY) for ensuring data privacy and security.
